# Walkthrough - Added Favicon

I have successfully added a custom favicon to the QuickXerox website.

## Changes
1.  **Created Facicon**: Generated a scalable SVG favicon ([/favicon.svg](file:///Users/hemanthmacbook/Desktop/QuickXerox/public/favicon.svg)) featuring a clean, blue design.
2.  **Updated HTML**: Modified [index.html](file:///Users/hemanthmacbook/Desktop/QuickXerox/index.html) to link to the new SVG file and removed the default Vite logo.
3.  **Deployed**: Built and deployed the changes to Firebase Hosting.

## Verification
The site has been deployed to `https://otp-project-aafc6.web.app`.
You should now see the new icon in your browser tab title bar.

> [!NOTE]
> If you still see the old icon, try doing a "Hard Refresh" (Cmd+Shift+R) or clearing your browser cache for the site.
